Patch Set 1:

I can't find the updated package in repositories. Any idea why it's not there?
I looked here:
http://download.tizen.org/snapshots/tizen/ivi/ivi-release/latest/repos/ivi/ia32/packages/i686/
and here:
http://download.tizen.org/releases/daily/tizen/ivi/ivi/latest/repos/ivi/ia32/packages/i686/

Patch Set 1:

It's not in 'ivi-release' because we carefully select what goes in the release branch (Tizen:IVI:Release).

It's not in 'ivi' daily because we have not created daily images for ivi (Tizen:IVI).

Should be in snapshots 'ivi'. https://download.tizen.org/snapshots/tizen/ivi/ivi/latest/

Patch Set 1:

Somehow https://download.tizen.org/snapshots/tizen/ivi/ivi/latest/repos/ivi/ia32/packages/i686/ has both the older and the newer package, and the older package has a higher release number, so it's fetched from the repo when doing a 'gbs build'. How to fix that?

The tag submit/tizen_ivi_milestone/20131113.054007 was pushed, but it was not completed because of the following reason(s):

- The tag means you want to submit commit 6ecb02705ec583bfd92ff8ead4b85b56d0f1858f in tizen_ivi_milestone branch to OBS, but this commit does NOT exist in tizen_ivi_milestone branch. Please use correct branch name as version in tag name submit/{version}/{date.time}.

Suggest to use "gbs submit" to trigger submission, or use following command to create tag "git tag submit/${version}/$(date --utc +%%Y%%m%%d.%%H%%M%%S) -m "****" ".
